<br>
Humanoid includes stuff like goo and underbulks but not drolvargs. Go figure out the logic in that.<br>
<br>
Pick pocket works up to 5 levels below your current level, so a level 60 can pick off a level 55 mob. One example would be picking in the upper kobold camp in Velketor's where you can get your pants pulled down by lots of silver coins if you should desire so. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ushakeyomen.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Shakey Omen</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_yellowspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/11/02 8:59:01 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousetrainingstudioqafornewbies.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=12967.topic&index=14>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Percent</span><hr size=1> It actually is coded at 2 percent, with a small (+1 to +3 percent) modifier based on a certain level of Dexterity. When you assume a very high dex for most rogues, and the fact you backstab/double several times a fight, you can get some astonishing backstab numbers.<br>
<br>
Assuming 200+ dex (going by tech logs it's 5 percent maximum), with 10 attempted backstabs, including doubles, on the average mob, you're talking about a 50 percent chance during the fight to pull one off. Our rogue parsed himself for fun, and ended up with a 37 percent assassination rate on 100 mobs.<br>
<br>
Fun, huh? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ucennyan.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Cennyan</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/11/02 11:09:43 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousetrainingstudioqafornewbies.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=12967.topic&index=15>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Percent</span><hr size=1> I dont know if the level limit is 49 though, I see friends of mine Assassinating mobs in Chardok that are blue still.  Not light blue, but blue.  That would mean they have to be at least 50  <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=550">Cennyan Evalion</a><br>
